required packages:
 sudo (for the initialisation of the database)
 mono-2.0-runtime (>= Mono 2.4.x), also winforms (Ict.Common.* dlls depend on it)
 on Debian eg.: apt-get -t lenny-backports install mono-runtime libmono-data2.0-cil libmono-system-web2.0-cil libmono-system-runtime2.0-cil libmono-winforms2.0-cil
 one of the following RDBMS:
   sqlite3 (requires > 3.6.1)
   postgresql (recommended, default)
   mysql

The default configuration for the server is to use postgresql. But mysql should now work as well.

Notes for sqlite:
If you want to use sqlite, you need to change the symbolic link:
cd etc30; rm PetraServerConsole.config; ln -s PetraServerConsole-sqlite.config PetraServerConsole.config
Sqlite requires quite a new version of sqlite, which might not be available on your distribution of Linux.
If you use sqlite, it will automatically create a copy of the demo database, and put it into your home directory: 
~/.config/OpenPetra.org/db30/petra.db

Notes for postgresql:
To load the initial database: 
sudo ./initpg.sh

Notes for mysql:
If you want to use mysql, you need to change the symbolic link:
cd etc30; rm PetraServerConsole.config; ln -s PetraServerConsole-mysql.config PetraServerConsole.config
To load the initial database (you need to know the db password for root, or change the script):
./initmysql.sh

firewall: 
in order for clients to connect from outside, you need to open ports 9000 and above (or what you have defined in your config files).
eg if you are using iptables, add such a line:
/sbin/iptables -A int-in -j ACCEPT -p tcp --dport 9000:9100

To start the server, type:

./openpetraorg-server.sh start

To see the menu and administrate the server, type:

./openpetraorg-server.sh menu

To stop the server, type:

./openpetraorg-server.sh stop

To start the client, type:

./startClient.sh

To operate the automated patching, you should run this:
ln -s /your/path/openpetraorg/patches30 /var/www/somekrypticLinkThatOnlyYourUsersNeedToKnowAndIsInTheRemoteClientConfigFile

To make OpenPetra.org start with the server, eg. in Debian/Ubuntu:
ln -s /your/path/openpetraorg/openpetraorg-server.sh /etc/init.d/openpetraorg
update-rc.d openpetraorg defaults